## Why this flow + design decisions (short)

* Use **quantized buckets** (kWh and price buckets) to reduce privacy leakage and gas cost.
* Use **commit–reveal** (commit = keccak(offer_hash|salt)) to keep private telemetry/salts off-chain until reveal.
* Use **EIP-712** typed signing of the structured offer (or of `offer_hash`) so signatures are unambiguous and replay-protected.
* Store only compact metadata and commit_hash on-chain; reveal (offer_data + salt) only when needed (reveal window).
* Provide off-chain P2P for low-latency local matching and optional on-chain commit for auditability.

