## Offer structure & quantization rules (recommended)

* `round_id` — monotonic market round integer (use chain block windows or server clock anchor)
* `node_id_hash` — bytes32 node id derived in Step1
* `offered_kwh_bucket` — small integer code representing quantized quantity (e.g., bucket 1 = 0.1–0.5 kWh, bucket 2 = 0.5–1.0)
* `price_bucket` — small integer price bucket (e.g., cents increments or buckets)
* `nonce` — uint32 monotonic per-node (prevents replay)
* `expiry_block` — block number after which reveal not allowed

Compose the offer payload as a deterministic ABI-encoding for hashing:
`abi.encodePacked(round_id, node_id_hash, offered_kwh_bucket, price_bucket, nonce, expiry_block)`

