## Security, privacy & anti-abuse checklist

* Quantize into buckets (do not store raw kWh/price on chain). ✔
* Use monotonic per-node `nonce` included in the offer and verified during reveal. ✔
* Enforce `expiry_block` to bound reveal window and prevent indefinite withholding. ✔
* Salt storage: POSIX `600` and optionally encrypt salt at rest. Do not back it up. ✔
* Prevent commit spam: require minimal collateral stake before `postCommit` accepted (check with `CollateralSC.deposits(nodeId) >= minDeposit`). Implement in `postCommit` the call to `CollateralSC` or have TradingSC check via `ICollateralSC` interface. ✔
* Anti-front-run: commit approach prevents a front-runner seeing offer content before reveal; still define reveal windows and stake slashing for no-reveal. ✔
* Timestamp & ordering: prefer block-based `roundId` or require server signed round anchor to mitigate local clock skew. ✔
* Signature domain separation: always use domain separation (EIP-712 or prefix) to avoid signature reuse. ✔

