## Operational notes & best practices

* Use small bucket tables stored in repo (human readable) explaining bucket → actual kWh/price range.
* For local matching, off-chain gossip (libp2p) should carry the full offer (without salt) — only participants in the local cluster see it.
* If optimizing privacy further, consider submitting only `offerHash` and let optimizer request reveals only for accepted matches.
* Provide an indexer that listens to `CommitPosted` events and builds an off-chain orderbook (for optimizer). Indexer should NOT store salts.
* In pilots, use short rounds (e.g., 5–15 min) so reveals and settlements happen quickly.

